Name {S3}: 3-methyl-1H-quinoxalin-2-one; Formula: C9H8N2O; Molecular Mass: 160.1726; Exact Mass: 160.0637; EA: C, 67.49; H, 5.03; N, 17.49; O, 9.99; Smiles: O=c1[nH]c2ccccc2nc1C;InChIKey: BMIMNRPAEPIYDN-UHFFFAOYSA-N

To a solution of 1,2-phenylenediamine (934 mg, 8.64 mmol, 1.00 equiv) in THF (20.0 mL) was added methyl-2-oxopropanoate (1.06 g, 942 μL, 10.4 mmol, 1.20 equiv). The solution was stirred at reflux for 2 h. The solution was then allowed to reach 21 °C. The formed precipitate was filtered. The remaining solution was reduced by half and filtered again (3x). HRMS–EI (m/z): [M]+ calcd for C9H8O1N2, 160.0637; found 160.0636.

The analytical data correspond those reported in the literature[1].
